**Case 1:** 

\- Description: It began on May 23rd, 2025, when someone named Dan contacted me via text message, saying they got my phone number from one Emilia on Zip Recruiter.  
Coincidentally, I lost my job 3 months ago with the federal government of Canada. They claim to be affiliated with eAccountable in Denver, Colorado. I was offered the position of Data Administrator, a monthly salary of $5800 USD, and additional commission, based on my investment level. My ability to withdraw was restricted once the deposit amount reached $20,000 USD, requesting more money to activate the large withdrawal channel. For every amount deposited, there was an excuse to have me deposit more, promising to release my funds if I complied. The platform is currently requesting $41,000 or I lose all funds. I lost a total of $86,567 USD to them.

The perpetrator gained the victim’s trust and convinced them to download and use a crypto wallet application under the pretext of making profitable investments. On 25 September, the victim’s funds were stolen from the wallet, indicating that the perpetrator had gained unauthorized access.

**Case 6:** 

Description: The victim, who manages an investment fund, was contacted via email by an individual using the address morphy@bursts.news, claiming to represent a podcast and requesting the victim's participation as a guest. As part of the setup, the victim was asked to share their screen while discussing websites of companies they were referencing, under the pretense of capturing visual content for the podcast.  
During the session, the perpetrators requested remote control access to the victim’s computer, claiming it was necessary for screen recording. Once access was granted, the attackers instructed the victim to perform certain actions and look away from the screen for "thumbnail" image purposes.  
At some point during the interaction, the attackers installed a spoofed version of MetaMask. They then instructed the victim to sign out of MetaMask and sign back in. With remote access and visibility of the login process, the attackers obtained the victim's MetaMask password and subsequently compromised the wallet.  
As a result of this coordinated social engineering attack, the perpetrators gained unauthorized access to the victim’s MetaMask wallet, which contained assets tied to the investment fund, and likely executed unauthorized transactions leading to asset theft.

Visualisation instruction: 

[https://pro.amlbot.com/visualizer/share/j27KQhR7O3xy2x5dSHHIWA](https://pro.amlbot.com/visualizer/share/j27KQhR7O3xy2x5dSHHIWA)

Как получить json

[https://api.amlbot.com/api/pro/share/{hash](https://api.amlbot.com/api/pro/share/{hash)}

Если в helpers isConnectionBasedMode: true игнорируй эту визуализацию

Далее все представление на дереве   
В payload 

Connects \- линии что связывают (edges) для простоты игнорируй там mergedEdge тип   
Items \- это ноды address/entity  
Txs \- ноды транзакций  
Comments \- это если нужны ноды комментарии соответственно

Принцип составления id (address-currency-token\_id) для адресов. Для entity slug/id вместо address  
Для транзакций hash-currency-token\_id-path. 

Далее есть helpers и в них   
txList соответственно вся информация о транзакциях на визуализации
